@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
    ViewData["CurrentYear"] = DateTime.Now.Year;
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"] - HealthyPaws</h1>

 <div class="container">
        
        <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong>12/12/2012</p>

        <p>At <strong>HealthyPaws</strong>, we respect the privacy of our users and are committed to protecting the personal information you share with us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect the medical information of pets within the <strong>HealthyPaws</strong> app.</p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect the following types of information to provide the best possible service for your pet’s health:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> Name, email, and contact information for the pet owner.</li>
            <li><strong>Pet Information:</strong> Medical history, breed, age, vaccination records, and other health-related information about your pet.</li>
            <li><strong>App Usage Information:</strong> Details on how the app is used, including interactions, features accessed, and other usage data.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the information collected to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Track and manage your pet’s medical history.</li>
            <li>Send reminders about vaccinations and appointments.</li>
            <li>Provide you with reports and health updates for your pet.</li>
            <li>Improve the app’s functionality and user experience.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <p>We do not share your pet’s medical information with third parties without your consent, except in the following circumstances:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> We may share your information with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating the app or providing services, but they are required to keep your information confidential.</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> We may disclose your information if required by law or to comply with legal processes, such as a subpoena or court order.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We take reasonable measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, or deletion. However, please be aware that no data transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure.</p>

        <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Access, update, or delete your pet’s medical information within the app.</li>
            <li>Request a copy of your personal data.</li>
            <li>Withdraw your consent to our processing of your data at any time by contacting us.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any significant changes by updating the "Effective Date" at the top of this page.</p>

        <h2>7. Contact Us</h2>
        <div class="contact-info">
            <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your pet’s medical information, please contact us at:</p>
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@healthypawsapp.com">support@healthypawsapp.com</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>